      "writtenOn": "2021-06-07T17:31:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Would be nice if this linked back to the original text block. It would make it trivial (and efficient) for clients to add decorations (e.g. you don\u0027t need to search through the string to locate the additional styling that needs to be done, such as underline). Pseudo-code:\n\n```\nvar builder \u003d new ShapedTextBuilder();\nvar block1 \u003d builder.addBlock(\u0027Hello \u0027, fontA);\nvar block2 \u003d builder.addBlock(\u0027World!\u0027, fontB);\n\nvar appStyles \u003d new Map();\nappStyles.set(block1, { underline: true });\nappStyles.set(block2, { color: \u0027#FF334455\u0027 });\n\nvar text \u003d builder.build();\nvar shaped \u003d text.shape(... layout constraints ...);\nvar lines \u003d shaped.lines;\nfor(var line of lines) {\n  for (var run on line.runs) {\n    var runStyle \u003d appStyles.get(run.block);\n    // render text and draw decorations (using `run` and `runStyle`)\n  }\n}\n```",
      "revId": "d7b8dc086b0039456c73f1a27a09a4f766c0f71e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
